decks.notes: This deck focuses on assembling a diverse array of creatures that can work together to create powerful synergies and combos. With cards like Chord of Calling and Yawgmoth, Thran Physician, players can quickly search for and deploy key creatures to the battlefield. By utilizing a toolbox approach, this deck can adapt to various situations and opponents, using cards like Grist, the Hunger Tide and Agatha's Soul Cauldron to control the board and win the game through strategic creature interactions and combos. By carefully selecting and sequencing creatures, players can outmaneuver their opponents and secure victory.

The UR Aggro deck focuses on fast, aggressive gameplay with low-cost spells and creatures that can quickly deal damage to the opponent. The key strategy is to use cheap burn spells like Lightning Bolt and Lava Dart to control the board and finish off opponents, while also utilizing creatures like Monastery Swiftspear and Dragon's Rage Channeler to apply pressure early in the game. The deck also includes cards like Mutagenic Growth and Mishra's Bauble for additional utility and card advantage. The deck aims to win quickly before the opponent can stabilize or mount a defense.

This deck focuses on aggressive creature-based gameplay using powerful threats like Tarmogoyf and Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer. It also utilizes disruptive spells like Thoughtseize and Fatal Push to control the game. The inclusion of Mishra's Research Desk and Urza's Saga provides additional card advantage and utility. The deck aims to pressure the opponent quickly while disrupting their game plan, ultimately overwhelming them with efficient creatures and spells. The companion card Jegantha, the Wellspring adds an extra layer of consistency and synergy to the deck.

The deck is focused on controlling the opponent's actions and board state through countering spells, removing threats, and utilizing powerful planeswalkers like Narset, Parter of Veils and Teferi, Time Raveler. The key card in the deck is The One Ring, which acts as a win condition while also providing card advantage and control options. The deck also includes various lands to fix mana and provide additional utility. By combining control elements with card advantage and a strong win condition, this deck aims to outmaneuver and outlast opponents in a 1 vs 1 format.

The main concept of this deck is to aggressively play low cost creatures and disruption spells to control the pace of the game. By utilizing Leyline of the Guildpact and Leyline Binding to protect your creatures and disrupt your opponent, along with cards like Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer and Scion of Draco to apply pressure, this deck aims to maintain tempo and control from the early turns of the game. Additionally, having Jegantha, the Wellspring as a companion adds consistency and potential late-game value to ensure your deck performs at its full potential.

The deck focuses on utilizing 5-color aggro creatures combined with Leyline of the Guildpact to maximize their effectiveness. The goal is to overwhelm the opponent with aggressive creatures such as Scion of Draco, Nishoba Brawler, and Tribal Flames, while also utilizing cards like Stubborn Denial and Lightning Bolt for disruption. Additionally, the inclusion of Ragavan, Nimble Pilferer provides card advantage and pressure. Jegantha, the Wellspring acts as a companion to further enhance the deck's consistency and synergy.

The deck focuses on disruptive spells, hand disruption, and removal to control the game. It utilizes powerful creatures and Planeswalkers to dominate the battlefield and grind out incremental advantages. The deck aims to outvalue and outlast the opponent by stripping their resources and overwhelming them with efficient spells and creatures. The archetype thrives on manipulation and destruction, leveraging a variety of tools to maintain control over the flow of the game and secure victory through attrition.

This deck focuses on aggressive play, utilizing a combination of efficient creatures and spells to deal damage quickly to the opponent. The deck includes a mix of low-cost creatures with powerful abilities, along with versatile spells like Tribal Flames and Lightning Bolt to control the board and finish off opponents. The inclusion of Jegantha, the Wellspring as a companion adds an extra layer of consistency to the deck. With a mana base that provides access to multiple colors, this deck aims to overwhelm opponents with a fast and versatile strategy.

The deck focuses on using control elements such as Lightning Bolt and Relic of Progenitus to disrupt the opponent's strategy while ramping up mana to quickly assemble the combo of Scapeshift and Valakut, the Molten Pinnacle for a game-winning amount of direct damage. The deck also utilizes cards like Wrenn and Six and Mishra's Bauble for card advantage and filtering, along with creatures like Dryad of the Ilysian Grove and Magda, the Hoardmaster to further support the overall game plan.
